  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "Sweet potato fries are delicious on their own, but you can enhance their flavor with a variety of toppings and dipping sauces. Here are some ideas:\n\n1. **Dipping Sauces:**\n   - **Chipotle mayo**: Mix mayonnaise with chipotle sauce for a smoky flavor.\n   - **Honey mustard**: A sweet and tangy sauce that complements the fries well.\n   - **Ranch dressing**: Creamy ranch adds a nice herbaceous touch.\n   - **Cilantro lime dressing**: Fresh and zesty; great for a fresh twist.\n   - **Sriracha or buffalo sauce**: For some heat.\n\n2. **Sprinkles & Seasonings:**\n   - **Sea salt**: A classic finish.\n   - **Garlic powder**: Adds a savory depth.\n   - **Cinnamon and sugar**: For a sweet treat, sprinkle some cinnamon and sugar over the fries.\n   - **Smoked paprika**: Adds a nice smokiness.\n   - **Parmesan cheese**: Grated and sprinkled on top for a savory kick.\n\n3. **Toppings:**\n   - **Chopped herbs**: Fresh parsley, cilantro, or green onions add freshness.\n   - **Feta or goat cheese**: Crumbled on top for a tangy flavor.\n   - **Avocado slices**: Creamy avocado pairs well with sweet potatoes.\n   - **Bacon bits**: Crispy bacon adds a savory crunch.\n   - **Jalape\u00f1os**: Fresh or pickled for some heat.\n\n4. **Combos:**\n   - **Loaded fries**: Top with cheese, jalape\u00f1os, sour cream, and chives for a loaded version.\n   - **Buffalo chicken fries**: Add shredded buffalo chicken, ranch, and green onions for a hearty option.\n   - **Guacamole**: A dollop of guacamole provides creaminess and flavor.\n\nFeel free to mix and match these ideas to create a sweet potato fries dish that suits your taste!",
